            category: 'Safe & Effective Care Environment',
            type: 'mcq',
            title: 'HCAHPS Top-Box Scoring',
            desc: 'A unit director reviews HCAHPS results. Which interpretation of the "top-box" methodology is correct?',
            choices: [
                { text: 'Only "Always" responses on frequency items count toward the publicly reported score', correct: true, log: 'Correct. Rationale: Top-box = most favorable response (e.g., Always for nurse communication). Reference: CMS HCAHPS 2024.' },
                { text: '"Usually" and "Always" are pooled into the top-box for reporting', log: 'Incorrect. Pooling Usually with Always understates true performance; CMS reports top-box only.' },
                { text: 'Top-box scoring applies only to overall hospital rating items', log: 'Incorrect. Top-box applies to composites such as nurse and doctor communication, not only overall rating.' },
                { text: 'Top-box is the percentage of patients who would not recommend the hospital', log: 'Incorrect. That metric is a separate "willingness to recommend" item, not a top-box definition.' },
            ],
